quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  32,23,"We gave Moses the Scripture, so do not doubt about meeting him, and We made it a guide for the Children of Israel"
  32,24,"We made some of them leaders, guiding by Our command, because they observed patience and firmly believed in Our signs"
  32,25,"Indeed, it is your Lord Who will judge between them on the Day of Resurrection concerning that over which they used to differ"
  32,26,"Is it not yet clear to them how many generations We destroyed before them, in whose dwellings they now walk about? Indeed, there are signs in this. Do they not then listen"
  32,27,"Do they not see that We drive water to parched land, producing thereby crops of which their cattle and they themselves eat? Do they not then see"
  32,28,"They say, “When will this Decision be if you are truthful?”"
  32,29,"Say, “On the Day of Decision the belief of those who disbelieved will not benefit them, nor will they be given any respite.”"
  32,30,So turn away from them and wait; they too are waiting